<% content_for(:page_title, 'Style Guide') %>

<div class="page-title">
  <h1>
    Style Guide
  </h1>
</div>

<p class="lead">Transition’s UI is powered by <a href="http://getbootstrap.com/2.3.2/base-css.html">bootstrap 2.3.2</a>, using <a href="https://github.com/thomas-mcdonald/bootstrap-sass/tree/v2.3.2.1">bootstrap SASS</a> (v2.3.2.1). This guide documents how transition is using bootstrap, where the app has diverged from default styles and any custom styles needed to fill in the gaps.</p>

<h2>Grid</h2>
<div class="row">
  <div class="span6">
    <p class="lead">Transition uses the <a href="http://getbootstrap.com/2.3.2/scaffolding.html#gridSystem">default bootstrap</a> <strong>12 column fixed responsive grid</strong>.</p>
    <p>Columns remain at their defined pixel widths until a certain breakpoint is reached. Breakpoints are at 1200px, 980px and 768px, after which the grid is linearised. Use a <a href="http://alefeuvre.github.io/foundation-grid-displayer/">grid overlay tool</a> to check alignment.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="span6">
    <div class="row add-bottom-margin">
      <div class="grid-example span1">span1</div>
      <div class="grid-example span2">span2</div>
      <div class="grid-example span3">span3</div>
    </div>
    <div class="row">
      <div class="grid-example span6">span6</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
<hr>

<h2>Page headers with subtitles</h2>
<div class="row">
  <p class="span6 lead">Page headers have a single pixel bottom-border. Subtitles - if used - run underneath this.</p>
  <section class="headers span6">
    <header>
      <div class="page-title">
        <h1>
          <span class="small">www.ukspaceagency.com</span>
          UK Space Agency
        </h1>
      </div>
      <p class="subtitle">UKSA is an executive agency of <a href="#">BIS</a></p>
      
      <div class="page-title with-border">
        <h1>
          <span class="small">www.ukspaceagency.com</span>
          UK Space Agency
        </h1>
      </div>
      <p class="subtitle">UKSA is an executive agency of <a href="#">BIS</a></p>
      
    </header>
  </section>
</div>
<hr>

<h2>Tables</h2>
<div class="row">
  <div class="span6 lead">
    <p>When using a table with two layers of headings, usually for interacting with table content, <code>table-header</code> and <code>table-header-secondary</code> classes are used.</p>
    
    <p>The second example shows a table with selectable rows. Selected rows highlight in yellow. The checkbox in the header selects all rows.</p>
  </div>
  <ul class="span6">
    <table class="table table-bordered table-hover">
      <thead>
        <tr class="table-header">
          <th>Primary header</th>
        </tr>
        <tr class="table-header-secondary">
          <th>Secondary header</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>Typical row</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Typical row</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
    </table>

    <table class="table table-bordered table-hover" data-module="selectable-table">
      <thead>
        <tr class="table-header">
          <th></th>
          <th>Primary header</th>
        </tr>
        <tr class="table-header-secondary">
          <th class="selectable-row">
            <div class="relative">
              <label>
                <input type="checkbox" class="js-toggle-all" />
              </label>
            </div>
          </th>
          <th><a href="#" class="btn">Action</a></th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr class="selected-row">
        <td class="selectable-row">
          <div class="relative">
            <label>
              <input type="checkbox" checked="checked" class="js-toggle-row" />
            </label>
          </div>
        </td>
        <td>Selected row</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="selectable-row">
          <div class="relative">
            <label>
              <input type="checkbox" />
            </label>
          </div>
        </td>
        <td>Typical row</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
    </table>

    <script>GOVUK.SelectableTable.setup();</script>
  </ul>
</div>
<hr>

<h2>Links</h2>
<div class="row">
  <div class="span6 lead">
    <p>To match bootstrap’s muted text, a muted link class is available.</p>
    <p>Transition has also added purple <code>:visited</code> styles. These apply to the main content but not to buttons.</p>
  </div>
  <ul class="span6">
    <a href="/style" class="muted-link">Muted link</a><br><br>
    <a href="/style">Visited link</a><br><br>
    <a href="/style#<%= "#{Time.now.utc.to_i}" %>">Normal link</a><br><br>
    <a href="/style" class="btn">Visited button link</a><br><br>
    <a href="/style" class="btn btn-success">Another visited button link</a><br><br>
  </ul>
</div>
<hr>

<h2>Buttons</h2>
<div class="row">
  <p class="span6 lead">Create and success actions use <code>btn-success</code>.</p>
  <div class="span6">
